	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Game balance?  I have to agree that not everything should be precisely balanced.  If it did then it would not reflect the average struggles of life, or even the fantastical interpretation of life that we play in EQ.<BR>
<BR>
As for my class, I researched just like everyone said.  I picked the class I would like to play most.  I ventured out into the game world, made alliances, and even helped to create a guild that grows every week with capable and qualified players.  <BR>
<BR>
But, like the ranger above, I am furious at the difficulty it takes to get in a group!  There are few in the guild right now that I can group with effectively (level differences).  So I spend LOTS of time going from zone to zone looking for a group.  From Karana to Rathe Moutntains, from Cazic Thule to Velious, I shout out the LFG thing.  Responses?  Few and far between.  One out of approimately every four times I log on, I find a group willing to include me.  And, each time I log, I spend a minimum of 45 minutes looking.<BR>
<BR>
VI says, &quot;Develop a relationship with people you can group with on a regular basis.&quot;  That is IF you are able to play on a regular basis.  But, like so many people, life gets in the way of my time that I want to spend playing.<BR>
<BR>
I'm not asking for a &quot;balance&quot;. I want VI to adjust my class to make it more worthwile to have in a group.  Very simple thing to do, when you could just add a spell or two.  <BR>
<BR>
In case you haven't already guessed it, I play a Wizard.  Evac?  That's apparently not enough of a reason for some.    2 or 5 pt damage shield?  Really...  that does alot...  oh yeah.<BR>
<BR>
And, to be honest, VI isn't wholly to blame for this.  The Wizard class is one of the hardest classes to play correctly.  The responsibility also goes to:<BR>
<BR>
1. those that never understood how to pace your casting and damage so as not to aggro the MOB on you instead of the tank. (Clerics shouldn't have to spend mana to keep a caster alive that continues to aggro the mob over and over, getting himself beaten severly) <BR>
<BR>
2. those that don't know the proper times and uses for AoE spells (big diaster if you don't know what you are doing)<BR>
<BR>
3. those that just use the latest spells at their level for damage, instead of balancing them with lower level spells<BR>
<BR>
4. those that don't know that an effective wizard can help PROTECT others in their party with a well placed spell, like Root or Enstill when there's one to many mobs on the tank, invisibility when crossing a bad area, or many other situations. <BR>
<BR>
All those Wizards that didn't take the time to learn proper spell use and stategy have burned ALOT of people, gotten alot of people killed, etc etc.  Sad, but true.<BR>
<BR>
I don't want special treatment for Wizzies.  I just want to be able to find a group and play this game.  And, if you can't do that, then how about a couple of spells that make soloing a better proposition?  <BR>
<BR>
Start another class you say?  I have several characters.  I still like to play the wizard class best, and hate it the most when I can't find a group.  All too often, that is case.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Macksin Shadizar<BR>
Officer-Merciless Justice<BR>
Veshaan<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
