			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It really sounds to me like the problem isn't a specific class being 'crappy' or they 'suck'.  Those are relative terms, they're a matter of opinion.  To me, it sounds like the role of some classes change too much at high levels.  Players spend a great deal of time with their character to build them to such a level, they obviously enjoy the play style or they wouldn't play it that long.  These drastic changes in group roles aren't fitting to the player.  Mid level play style should be like high level play style.<BR>
<BR>
The other problem I see is classes who aren't wanted.  If a class can't directly help a group, chances are the group doesn't want them.  Why should we bring the necro along if he helps the most when things go wrong?  When planning a raid, you'd like to think of being successful, not getting killed and having to summon your corpse to get a res.  Although the class may play a role, other players don't see that role as important enough to seek them out for their group.<BR>
<BR>
Just my thoughts,<BR>
 Typodaemon
				</font>
			</td>

